BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:1a4b8259-b610-49fe-bb33-99bda0a9300c
DTSTAMP:20260717T011518Z
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260720T180000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260720T193000
SUMMARY:Week 1: Launch — Foundation
DESCRIPTION:WEEK 1 — PHASE 1: Foundation\nBLOCK WEEK 1: Build\nTARGET: RP
 E 6–7\nLeave 3–4 good reps in reserve.\n\nTODAY’S OBJECTIVE: Acceleratio
 n + posterior-chain strength\n\nWARM-UP\n• Jump rope or easy jog – 3 min
 utes\n• Hip Halo – 10 each direction\n• World’s Greatest Stretch – 5/sid
 e\n• Toe sweeps – 10\n• Open books – 8/side\n• Band pass-through – 15\n•
  Crossover Symmetry activation\n\nSPRINT WORK\n• 10 yd sprint – 5 reps\n
 • 20 yd sprint – 4 reps\n• 30 yd sprint – 2 reps\n• Full recovery: 2–3 m
 inutes between full-speed reps\n\nPLYOMETRICS\n• Box jump – 3 x 4\n• Bro
 ad jump – 3 x 3\n• Bounds – 2 x 15 yd\n\nSTRENGTH\n• Trap Bar Deadlift –
  3 x 8 @ RPE 6–7\n• Pull-ups or assisted pull-ups – 3 x 6–8\n• Chest-sup
 ported DB row – 3 x 8\n• 1-arm DB row – 3 x 8/side\n• Face pull – 3 x 15
 \n• Farmer carry – 3 x 30–40 yd\n\nBASEBALL WORK\n• Long toss – 12–18 mi
 nutes\n• Finish with 8–10 firm throws\; stop if arm action changes\n\nTR
 ACKING\nRecord weight used\, sets/reps completed\, RPE\, sprint times wh
 en measured\, soreness\, and notes.\nPain rule: stop any exercise or thr
 ow that causes sharp pain.
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
BEGIN:VALARM
TRIGGER:-PT60M
ACTION:DISPLAY
DESCRIPTION:Week 1: Launch — Foundation
END:VALARM
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:ffc874b1-e2dd-43a5-8aa1-dccc2e378205
DTSTAMP:20260717T011518Z
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260721T180000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260721T191500
SUMMARY:Week 1: Ignite — Foundation
DESCRIPTION:WEEK 1 — PHASE 1: Foundation\nBLOCK WEEK 1: Build\nTARGET: RP
 E 6–7\nLeave 3–4 good reps in reserve.\n\nTODAY’S OBJECTIVE: Upper-body 
 strength + rotational power\n\nWARM-UP\n• Jump rope or easy jog – 3 minu
 tes\n• Hip Halo – 10 each direction\n• World’s Greatest Stretch – 5/side
 \n• Toe sweeps – 10\n• Open books – 8/side\n• Band pass-through – 15\n• 
 Crossover Symmetry activation\n\nMED-BALL POWER\n• Rotational scoop toss
  – 4 x 4/side\n• Shot-put throw – 3 x 4/side\n• Overhead slam – 3 x 5\n•
  Every throw should be explosive\; stop before speed drops\n\nSTRENGTH\n
 • Incline DB press – 3 x 8 @ RPE 6–7\n• Half-kneeling landmine press – 3
  x 8/arm\n• Weighted or tempo push-up – 3 x 8–12\n• DB floor press – 3 x
  8\n• Band triceps pressdown – 3 x 12\n• Y-T-W raises – 2 x 8 each\n\nBA
 SEBALL WORK\n• Tee work – 40 swings\n• Front toss – 25 swings\n• Finish 
 with 10 hard line drives to the middle/opposite field\n\nTRACKING\nRecor
 d weight used\, sets/reps completed\, RPE\, sprint times when measured\,
  soreness\, and notes.\nPain rule: stop any exercise or throw that cause
 s sharp pain.
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
BEGIN:VALARM
TRIGGER:-PT60M
ACTION:DISPLAY
DESCRIPTION:Week 1: Ignite — Foundation
END:VALARM
END:VEVENT
