 E 6–7\nLeave 3–4 good reps in reserve.\n\nTODAY’S OBJECTIVE: Maximum spe
 ed + shoulder durability\n\nWARM-UP\n• Jump rope or easy jog – 3 minutes
 \n• Hip Halo – 10 each direction\n• World’s Greatest Stretch – 5/side\n•
  Toe sweeps – 10\n• Open books – 8/side\n• Band pass-through – 15\n• Cro
 ssover Symmetry activation\n\nSPRINT WORK\n• Flying 10 – 5 reps\n• Build
 -up run – 3 reps\n• Full recovery between all fast reps\n\nPLYOMETRICS\n
 • Pogos – 3 x 20\n• Line or mini-hurdle hops – 3 x 5\n• Stick landing – 
 2 x 4\n\nSTRENGTH / ARM CARE\n• 1-arm DB or landmine shoulder press – 3 
 x 8/arm\n• Rear-delt fly – 3 x 12\n• Face pull – 3 x 15\n• Band external
  rotation – 2 x 12/side\n• Crossover Symmetry recovery\n\nBASEBALL WORK\
 n• Older player: 20–30 pitch bullpen or high-intent flat ground\, per th
 rowing plan\n• Younger player: 20–25 controlled flat-ground throws focus
 ed on mechanics\n• No max-effort pitching when sore or after a game-heav
 y week\n\nTRACKING\nRecord weight used\, sets/reps completed\, RPE\, spr
 int times when measured\, soreness\, and notes.\nPain rule: stop any exe
 rcise or throw that causes sharp pain.
