DESCRIPTION:WEEK 1 — PHASE 1: Foundation\nBLOCK WEEK 1: Build\nTARGET: RP
 E 6–7\nLeave 3–4 good reps in reserve.\n\nTODAY’S OBJECTIVE: Transfer tr
 aining to baseball\nQuality over quantity. Finish before mechanics fade.
 \n\nWARM-UP\n• Dynamic warm-up – 8–10 minutes\n• Progressive throwing\n\
 nTHROWING\n• Long toss or position-specific throwing – 15–20 minutes\n\n
 DEFENSE\n• Position work – 20–30 minutes\n• Include game-speed first ste
 ps and throws\n\nHITTING\n• Tee work – 25 swings\n• Front toss – 25 swin
 gs\n• Live or machine work – 20–30 swings\n\nBASERUNNING\n• Starts – 4 r
 eps\n• Home-to-first – 3 reps\n• First-to-third route – 3 reps\n\nOPTION
 AL CONDITIONING\n• 6 x 80–100 yd tempo runs at about 70% only when legs 
 feel good\n\nTRACKING\nRecord weight used\, sets/reps completed\, RPE\, 
 sprint times when measured\, soreness\, and notes.\nPain rule: stop any 
 exercise or throw that causes sharp pain.
