 5/side\n• Toe sweeps – 10\n• Open books – 8/side\n• Band pass-through – 
 15\n• Crossover Symmetry activation\n\nSPRINT WORK\n• Base-steal start –
  4/side\n• 10 yd sprint – 4 reps\n• 30 yd sprint – 4 reps\n• Full recove
 ry: 2–3 minutes between full-speed reps\n\nPLYOMETRICS\n• Base-steal cro
 ssover bound – 3 x 4/side\n• Broad jump – 4 x 2\n• Pogo jump – 3 x 20\n\
 nSTRENGTH\n• Trap Bar Deadlift – 4 x 4 @ RPE 6–7\n• Pull-ups or assisted
  pull-ups – 3 x 6–8\n• Chest-supported DB row – 3 x 8\n• 1-arm DB row – 
 3 x 8/side\n• Face pull – 3 x 15\n• Farmer carry – 3 x 30–40 yd\n\nBASEB
 ALL WORK\n• Long toss – 12–18 minutes\n• Finish with 8–10 firm throws\; 
 stop if arm action changes\n\nTRACKING\nRecord weight used\, sets/reps c
 ompleted\, RPE\, sprint times when measured\, soreness\, and notes.\nPai
 n rule: stop any exercise or throw that causes sharp pain.
