SUMMARY:Week 19: Ignite — Baseball Speed
DESCRIPTION:WEEK 19 — PHASE 5: Baseball Speed\nBLOCK WEEK 3: Challenge\nT
 ARGET: RPE 7–8\nUse the heaviest clean weight of the block\; no grinding
 .\n\nTODAY’S OBJECTIVE: Upper-body strength + rotational power\n\nWARM-U
 P\n• Jump rope or easy jog – 3 minutes\n• Hip Halo – 10 each direction\n
 • World’s Greatest Stretch – 5/side\n• Toe sweeps – 10\n• Open books – 8
 /side\n• Band pass-through – 15\n• Crossover Symmetry activation\n\nMED-
 BALL POWER\n• Open-stance scoop toss – 4 x 3/side\n• Walk-in shot-put th
 row – 4 x 3/side\n• Overhead slam – 3 x 5\n• Every throw should be explo
 sive\; stop before speed drops\n\nSTRENGTH\n• Incline DB press – 5 x 2 @
  RPE 7–8\n• Half-kneeling landmine press – 3 x 8/arm\n• Weighted or temp
 o push-up – 3 x 8–12\n• DB floor press – 3 x 8\n• Band triceps pressdown
  – 3 x 12\n• Y-T-W raises – 2 x 8 each\n\nBASEBALL WORK\n• Tee work – 40
  swings\n• Front toss – 25 swings\n• Finish with 10 hard line drives to 
 the middle/opposite field\n\nTRACKING\nRecord weight used\, sets/reps co
 mpleted\, RPE\, sprint times when measured\, soreness\, and notes.\nPain
  rule: stop any exercise or throw that causes sharp pain.
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
BEGIN:VALARM
TRIGGER:-PT60M
ACTION:DISPLAY
DESCRIPTION:Week 19: Ignite — Baseball Speed
END:VALARM
END:VEVENT
