SUMMARY:Week 24: Launch — Peak & Test
DESCRIPTION:WEEK 24 — PHASE 6: Peak & Test\nBLOCK WEEK 4: Deload / Retest
 \nTARGET: RPE 5–6\nReduce lifting volume about 35–40%\; move fast and re
 test only when fresh.\n\nTODAY’S OBJECTIVE: Acceleration + posterior-cha
 in strength\n\nWARM-UP\n• Jump rope or easy jog – 3 minutes\n• Hip Halo 
 – 10 each direction\n• World’s Greatest Stretch – 5/side\n• Toe sweeps –
  10\n• Open books – 8/side\n• Band pass-through – 15\n• Crossover Symmet
 ry activation\n\nSPRINT WORK\n• 10 yd sprint – 3 reps\n• 30 yd sprint – 
 3 reps\n• Full recovery: 2–3 minutes between full-speed reps\n\nPLYOMETR
 ICS\n• Broad jump – 2 x 2\n• Box jump – 2 x 3\n\nSTRENGTH\n• Trap Bar De
 adlift – 2 x 5 @ RPE 5–6\n• Pull-ups or assisted pull-ups – 2 x 6–8\n• C
 hest-supported DB row – 2 x 8\n• 1-arm DB row – 2 x 8/side\n• Face pull 
 – 2 x 12\n• Farmer carry – 2 x 25 yd\n\nBASEBALL WORK\n• Long toss – 12–
 18 minutes\n• Finish with 8–10 firm throws\; stop if arm action changes\
 n\nTRACKING\nRecord weight used\, sets/reps completed\, RPE\, sprint tim
 es when measured\, soreness\, and notes.\nPain rule: stop any exercise o
 r throw that causes sharp pain.
